## Introduction
In linux, we can request some ip query interface through `curl` to view the current public `ip` address
## Command Line
View current ip address
```bash
curl ifconfig.me
```
## Parameter
| parameter | Introduction                                                               |
| --------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| curl   |is  a  tool to transfer data from or to a server, using one of the supported protocols (DICT, FILE, FTP, FTPS, GOPHER, HTTP, HTTPS, IMAP, IMAPS, LDAP, LDAPS,
       POP3, POP3S, RTMP, RTSP, SCP, SFTP, SMB, SMBS, SMTP, SMTPS, TELNET and TFTP). The command is designed to work without user interaction.|
###  operation result
```
x.22.85.x
```
### More information
You can also query through these URLs
```bash
curl ipinfo.io/ip
curl api.ipify.org
curl checkip.dyndns.org
curl ident.me
curl bot.whatismyipaddress.com
curl ipecho.net/plain
```
